## README.md
### Python Quickstart Guide
#### Install Required Libraries
To run this application, you must first install the required libraries. You can do so by running:
```bash
pip install pydantic fastapi uvicorn
```
#### Clone Project Directory
Clone the repository to your preferred directory.

#### Set Up Application Environment
To use the FastAPI application, you need an environment with Python 3.7 or higher and pip installed.
*   Create a `.env` file in your project root:
    ```bash
# .env example content
KEY=' SECRET_KEY'
```

Setup a secret key by entering it into your `.env` file.

#### Start the FastAPI Application
To start the application, use:
```bash
uvicorn main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000
```
This will start the server and open the default web browser to `http://127.0.0.1:8000/`.

You can now view your created account:

    *   Register yourself as a user using HTTP POST to [http://127.0.0.1:8000/users](http://127.0.0.1:8000/users)

### Security Considerations
-   Ensure that you are testing the application in a suitable secure environment.
-   Use HTTPS (SSL/TLS) when hosting this service.
-   Do not hard-code your database credentials for security reasons; store them securely.

To view user data, use HTTP GET to [http://127.0.0.1:8000/users](http://127.0.0.1:8000/users).

Make any necessary adjustments before deploying the application in a production environment.

